President Cyril Ramaphosa is hoping the Boks book his ticket to the Rugby World Cup final. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is hoping the Boks will book his ticket to the Rugby World Cup final. He video called Springboks captain, Siya Kolisi to wish the team all the best for their semi-final clash with Wales on Sunday. READ: England beat All Blacks to advance to World Cup final “I am so proud of you personally and of the team as well. You have done extremely well and I wish you well for the semi-final. You have 57 million South Africans behind you.” Ramaphosa assured Kolisi that he will be in Japan to lift the trophy. The winning team between the Boks and Wales will face England for the final.